- download iso
- go to system > administration -> startup disk creator
	and point to iso and the target usb
- restart system, go to bios and boot from usb
- install and configure

- install vim, sudo apt-get install vim
- install git 
	- sudo add-apt-repository ppa:git-core/ppa
	- sudo apt-get update
	- sudo apt-get install git
  then git --version
  then git clone <repo url from github>

- themes
	- to change themes go to applications > utilites > tweaks
	- change appearance setting
	- enable arc, and then curson and icons dmz-black
	- to enable shell extensions, go to extensions in tweak tool and
	  and enable user themes, restart tweaks took and select arc theme

- install arc dark theme
	- sudo sh -c "echo 'deb http://download.opensuse.org/repositories/home:/Horst3180/xUbuntu_16.04/ /' >> /etc/apt/sources.list.d/arc-theme.list"
	- sudo apt-get update && sudo apt-get install arc-theme	
    	- Open Unity Tweak Tool
    	- Go to Appearance > Theme
    	- Select ‘Arc’


